pullRequest.body:
This file now has the lead in the number of CPU instructions amongst all of mathlib. The majority come from `linarith` being an `autoparam` for many definitions, often in multiple arguments. This uses `omega` in place of `linarith` to improve performance.

nodes.body: !bench

Here are the [benchmark results](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/run-detail/d25994b0-9dcc-4377-bb06-3a83a5642bd5) for commit 57e9eaccb4cff08568b538393d1552f25787b61c.
There were [significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/9fe959aa-62f1-4e00-8003-2c749289a207/to/d25994b0-9dcc-4377-bb06-3a83a5642bd5) against commit cabd20e08a0f38867bc88d3b25bd55c60f71052f:
```diff
  Benchmark                                            Metric             Change
  ==============================================================================
+ build                                                tactic execution    -7.8%
+ ~Mathlib.Algebra.Homology.ExactSequence              instructions       -10.0%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Abelian.DiagramLemmas.Four   instructions       -69.8%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.ComposableArrows             instructions       -46.3%
```

There were [significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/9fe959aa-62f1-4e00-8003-2c749289a207/to/f5a1d6e3-8ca7-4f9a-93d2-5024c5664dc1) against commit cabd20e08a0f38867bc88d3b25bd55c60f71052f:


There were [significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/4dee61c5-c450-4a1f-a057-b55b74ddbb05/to/24cad562-823b-45b9-944b-2d3b67dde90b) against commit 68612e920cc8423456cf7b990cceaa8e16a08230:
